.\" Man page for perf-tests.sh
.TH PERF-TESTS 1 "2024" "RustOwl" "RustOwl Performance Testing"
.SH NAME
perf-tests.sh \- Performance testing and regression analysis for RustOwl
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B perf-tests.sh
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBperf-tests.sh\fR script provides comprehensive performance testing and regression analysis for RustOwl. It compares the current code changes against a baseline version by automatically managing git stashes, building both versions, and measuring various performance metrics.

The script is designed to help developers validate that their changes don't introduce performance regressions while also detecting genuine performance improvements.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.TP
.B \-\-verify
Check the testing environment without running performance tests. Shows git status, existing binaries, and system information.
.TP
.B \-\-prepare
Build both baseline and current versions separately without running performance comparisons. Useful for pre-building binaries.
.TP
.B \-\-compare
Run performance comparisons on pre-built binaries. Requires that \fB\-\-prepare\fR has been run first.
.TP
.B \-\-stability
Run multiple iterations of performance tests to check measurement consistency and detect unstable results.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Force rebuild of existing binaries even if they already exist.
.TP
.B \-\-cold
Clear system caches before each performance test. This provides more consistent and realistic measurements by eliminating cache effects.

.SH TESTING MODES
.SS Default Mode
When run without arguments, the script performs a complete automated test:
.IP 1. 4
Verifies git repository state
.IP 2. 4
Stashes current changes (if any)
.IP 3. 4
Builds baseline version
.IP 4. 4
Restores changes and builds current version
.IP 5. 4
Runs performance comparisons
.IP 6. 4
Cleans up temporary files

.SS Stepwise Testing
For more control, use the stepwise testing options:

.B \-\-verify
to check environment setup

.B \-\-prepare
to build both versions

.B \-\-compare
to run performance tests

.B \-\-stability
to validate result consistency

.SH MEASUREMENTS
The script provides comprehensive analysis across multiple dimensions:

.SS Binary Analysis
.IP \(bu 4
Binary size comparison with percentage differences
.IP \(bu 4
Symbol count analysis (requires \fBnm\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Strip analysis showing debug symbol overhead
.IP \(bu 4
SHA256 hash verification to ensure different binaries

.SS Performance Metrics
.IP \(bu 4
Execution time (wall clock)
.IP \(bu 4
Peak memory usage (RSS)
.IP \(bu 4
Page faults (major/minor)
.IP \(bu 4
Context switches (voluntary/involuntary)

.SS Advanced Analysis
When optional tools are available:
.IP \(bu 4
Statistical benchmarking with confidence intervals (\fBhyperfine\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Memory profiling with heap analysis (\fBvalgrind\fR on Linux)
.IP \(bu 4
CPU profiling recommendations

.SS Verification Features
.IP \(bu 4
Git workflow validation (stash/unstash operations)
.IP \(bu 4
Binary functionality testing before measurement
.IP \(bu 4
Environment sanity checks

.SH CACHE MANAGEMENT
Performance measurements can be significantly affected by various system caches. The \fB\-\-cold\fR option addresses this by clearing:

.SS Filesystem Caches
.IP \(bu 4
macOS: Uses \fBpurge\fR command
.IP \(bu 4
Linux: Drops page cache via \fB/proc/sys/vm/drop_caches\fR

.SS Build Caches
.IP \(bu 4
Cargo incremental compilation cache
.IP \(bu 4
Rust compilation artifacts

.SS CPU Caches
.IP \(bu 4
L1/L2/L3 instruction and data caches
.IP \(bu 4
Branch prediction tables

.PP
\fBNote:\fR Cache clearing may require sudo privileges on some systems.

.SH DEPENDENCIES
.SS Required
