.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh
Run complete automated performance test
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh \-\-cold
Run test with cache clearing for consistent results
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh \-\-verify
Check environment and show current state
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh \-\-prepare && perf-tests.sh \-\-compare
Build versions separately, then test
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh \-\-stability
Run multiple iterations to check measurement consistency

.SH INTERPRETING RESULTS
.SS Binary Size Changes
.IP \(bu 4
Positive percentage: Binary grew (potential concern)
.IP \(bu 4
Negative percentage: Binary shrunk (potential improvement)
.IP \(bu 4
Identical sizes with different code: Investigation needed

.SS Performance Changes
.IP \(bu 4
Execution time: Lower is better
.IP \(bu 4
Memory usage: Lower is generally better
.IP \(bu 4
Page faults: Lower indicates better memory efficiency
.IP \(bu 4
Context switches: Lower may indicate better CPU utilization

.SS Cache Effects
.IP \(bu 4
First run (cold): Realistic user experience
.IP \(bu 4
Subsequent runs (warm): Optimistic results
.IP \(bu 4
Large variations: Consider using \fB\-\-cold\fR or \fB\-\-stability\fR

.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.SS Common Issues
.TP
.B Identical binary sizes with different SHA256 hashes
The binaries contain different metadata but identical code. This can happen with timestamp differences or debug information.

.TP
.B Large performance variations between runs
System load or cache effects. Use \fB\-\-cold\fR for consistency or \fB\-\-stability\fR to check variation.

.TP
.B "Uncommitted changes" warnings
The script detects uncommitted changes and will stash them. Ensure important work is committed first.

.TP
.B Permission denied on cache clearing
Cache clearing may require sudo privileges. The script will continue without clearing caches if permissions are insufficient.

.SS Debug Information
Use \fB\-\-verify\fR to check:
.IP \(bu 4
Git repository status
.IP \(bu 4
Existing binary states
.IP \(bu 4
Available tools and dependencies
.IP \(bu 4
System information

.SH FILES
