.B rustowl-baseline
Baseline binary for comparison
.TP
.B rustowl-current
Current version binary
.TP
.B rustowlc-baseline
Baseline compiler binary
.TP
.B rustowlc-current
Current compiler binary

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CARGO_TARGET_DIR
Cargo build directory (default: target/)
.TP
.B RUST_BACKTRACE
Set to 1 for detailed error traces
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable colored output

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (missing tools, build failure)
.TP
.B 2
Git repository issues
.TP
.B 3
Binary verification failure

.SH NOTES
This script is designed for development and CI/CD environments. It requires a clean git working directory or will automatically stash changes.

For accurate performance measurements, consider running multiple iterations and using the \fB\-\-cold\fR option to eliminate cache effects.

The script prioritizes reproducibility and verification over raw speed, making it suitable for regression testing and performance validation.

