.SH AUTHOR
RustOwl development team
              Runs the complete workflow: prepare environment, build both versions, and
              compare performance. This is the standard mode for most use cases.

       Stepwise Testing
              Break the testing process into individual steps for debugging or detailed
              analysis:
              1. --verify   : Check environment
              2. --prepare  : Build both versions
              3. --stability: Multi-iteration testing
              4. --compare  : Performance comparison

MEASUREMENTS
       Binary Analysis
              • Binary size comparison with percentage differences
              • Symbol count analysis (if nm is available)
              • Strip analysis showing debug symbol overhead

       Performance Metrics
              • Execution time (wall clock)
              • Peak memory usage (RSS - Resident Set Size)
              • Page faults (major/minor indicating I/O and memory pressure)
              • Context switches (voluntary/involuntary revealing scheduling behavior)

       Verification Features
              • SHA256 hash comparison to ensure different binaries
              • Git workflow validation (stash/unstash operations)
              • Binary functionality testing before measurement
              • Multi-iteration stability checking

CACHE EFFECTS
       Performance measurements are significantly affected by system caches. First runs
       typically show "cold" performance with full disk I/O, while subsequent runs show
       "warm" performance with cached data.

       Common Cache Types:
              • Filesystem cache (page cache) - Most significant impact
              • Binary/library cache - Dynamic linker caching
              • CPU caches - L1/L2/L3 and branch prediction
              • Rust build cache - Incremental compilation artifacts

       Cache Clearing:
              macOS: sudo purge
              Linux: sudo sync && echo 3 | sudo tee /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
              Rust:  cargo clean

       Use --cold option for automated cache clearing between tests.

TOOL REQUIREMENTS
       Required Tools
              git    - Version control operations
              cargo  - Rust build system  
              bc     - Mathematical calculations

       Optional Tools
              hyperfine - Statistical benchmarking with confidence intervals
              valgrind  - Memory profiling (Linux only)
              perf      - CPU profiling (Linux only)
              nm        - Symbol table analysis
              strip     - Debug symbol removal

       The script automatically detects available tools and adapts functionality accordingly.
       Missing optional tools will show installation suggestions.

RESULT INTERPRETATION
       Normal Results
              • Small performance differences (<2x)
              • Consistent results across multiple runs
              • Different binary hashes for baseline vs current

       Suspicious Results (Investigate Further)
              • Identical binary hashes (no code changes detected)
              • Extreme performance differences (>10x)
              • Zero page faults (suggests warm cache or measurement issues)
              • High variation between runs (>2x difference)

       Best Practices
              • Run --verify first to check environment
              • Use --stability for significant performance claims
              • Test on quiet systems with minimal background processes
              • Consider both cold and warm performance metrics
              • Run multiple times to confirm consistency

EXAMPLES
       Basic performance test:
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh

       Debug suspicious results:
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh --verify
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh --prepare --force
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh --stability

       Cold performance testing:
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh --cold

       Build and test separately:
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh --prepare
              ./scripts/perf-tests.sh --compare

EXIT STATUS
       0      Success
       1      Missing required tools or build failure
       2      Invalid command line arguments

FILES
       ./rustowl-baseline     Temporary baseline binary
       ./rustowl-current      Temporary current binary
       ./rustowlc-baseline    Temporary baseline compiler binary
       ./rustowlc-current     Temporary current compiler binary

       These files are automatically cleaned up after testing unless the script fails.

ENVIRONMENT
       RUSTC_BOOTSTRAP        May be set for stable compiler builds
       CARGO_TARGET_DIR       Custom target directory for builds

